Stripe&rsquo;s cofounders published an annual letter to their users. Things that caught my eye in this 2021 business update are:
  Rise of the creator economy &ldquo;Creator economy, a term that refers to directing payments to those creating content or products on internet platforms: think developers on GitHub, podcasters on Spotify, or the Twitterati on Twitter all getting paid directly for their creations.&rdquo;
  Rise of embedded finance &ldquo;&hellip; the explosive growth in fintech &hellip; platforms are now integrating additional financial services directly into their products, such as business expense cards, monetary accounts, and loan access.

 &ldquo;Why me?&rdquo;
&ldquo;That is a very Earthling question to ask, Mr. Pilgrim. Why you? Why us for that matter? Why anything? Because this moment simply is.&rdquo;
  From Slaughterhouse-Five

The chances of success for an application increases when the following set of people are happy:
###Administrators
Administrators want to easily &hellip;
 Install and uninstall, and does not leave anything behind after uninstall Configure and customize system settings Keep things updated without crying Full control over email support  ###Policy deciders
Policy deciders want to &hellip;
 Control who can access the application Decide who can perform certain operations Keep tabs on who has done what  ###Users
